translate ru strings:

    old "When Sarah arrived at the Great Hall, the room was already buzzing with the voices of the countless guests."
    new "When Sarah arrived at the Great Hall, the room was already buzzing with the voices of the countless guests."

    old "Peering in through the narrow gap in the door, she could see most of them."
    new "Peering in through the narrow gap in the door, she could see most of them."

    old "Nobles, from the lowest ranks to the highest, pressed into the room."
    new "Nobles, from the lowest ranks to the highest, pressed into the room."

    old "This was an event that none of them would have missed, no matter what."
    new "This was an event that none of them would have missed, no matter what."

    old "Then, the trumpets blared and the servants pulled open the door."
    new "Then, the trumpets blared and the servants pulled open the door."

    old "Sarah saw a sea of heads, turning about, all looking at her."
    new "Sarah saw a sea of heads, turning about, all looking at her."

    old "She had been no stranger to being the center of attention, but this was nearly too much, even for her."
    new "She had been no stranger to being the center of attention, but this was nearly too much, even for her."

    old "Slowly, the musicians transitioned from the music announcing her arrival, to the song of her family."
    new "Slowly, the musicians transitioned from the music announcing her arrival, to the song of her family."

    old "A song, centuries old, celebrating the battle where her ancestor won his crown."
    new "A song, centuries old, celebrating the battle where her ancestor won his crown."

    old "A crown her family still wore, to this day."
    new "A crown her family still wore, to this day."

    old "Sarah slowly began to walk, careful to keep both herself and the dress in balance."
    new "Sarah slowly began to walk, careful to keep both herself and the dress in balance."

    old "The thing weighed a ton."
    new "The thing weighed a ton."

    old "And men thought they had it hard, wearing their armors."
    new "And men thought they had it hard, wearing their armors."

    old "She smiled to herself as she strode down the carpet."
    new "She smiled to herself as she strode down the carpet."

    old "Walking between the seated nobles, she heard their soft whispers."
    new "Walking between the seated nobles, she heard their soft whispers."

    old "All the same."
    new "All the same."

    old "How beautiful she was."
    new "How beautiful she was."

    old "How proud her parents would have been."
    new "How proud her parents would have been."

    old "Sarah could feel her emotions roaring inside of her heart."
    new "Sarah could feel her emotions roaring inside of her heart."

    old "But she had spend a lifetime perfecting the art of the public face, and she showed not a hint of her turmoil."
    new "But she had spend a lifetime perfecting the art of the public face, and she showed not a hint of her turmoil."

    old "Composed, she neared the end of the carpet when she finally looked up at him."
    new "Composed, she neared the end of the carpet when she finally looked up at him."

    old "There, looking back at her, his perfect smile."
    new "There, looking back at her, his perfect smile."

    old "He was wearing his military uniform."
    new "He was wearing his military uniform."

    old "Much like the man himself, not a hair or a fiber, out of place."
    new "Much like the man himself, not a hair or a fiber, out of place."

    old "Just as she radiated the essence of a Rossanian bride, so did he the groom."
    new "Just as she radiated the essence of a Rossanian bride, so did he the groom."

    old "Two perfect players, in this perfect performance."
    new "Two perfect players, in this perfect performance."

    old "And for a brief moment, she could not help but be swepped up in it, as likely all the guests were."
    new "And for a brief moment, she could not help but be swepped up in it, as likely all the guests were."

    old "He was handsome."
    new "He was handsome."

    old "He was in many ways, everything that the books of her youth had promised her she would want."
    new "He was in many ways, everything that the books of her youth had promised her she would want."

    old "Strong. Of noble blood. Brave."
    new "Strong. Of noble blood. Brave."

    old "Yet all these were but reasons to her mind, not words to her heart."
    new "Yet all these were but reasons to her mind, not words to her heart."

    old "And Sarah felt the smallest hint of regret."
    new "And Sarah felt the smallest hint of regret."

    old "As if she had discovered the smallest of imperfections in something otherwise flawless."
    new "As if she had discovered the smallest of imperfections in something otherwise flawless."

    old "And that for its otherwise flawless nature, the singular flaw, was made so much worse."
    new "And that for its otherwise flawless nature, the singular flaw, was made so much worse."

    old "Impossible to ignore."
    new "Impossible to ignore."

    old "Love."
    new "Love."

    old "What was all this without love?"
    new "What was all this without love?"

    old "Did he hold these same doubts as her, she wondered."
    new "Did he hold these same doubts as her, she wondered."

    old "He showed not a hint of it, but then again, neither did she show her own struggles."
    new "He showed not a hint of it, but then again, neither did she show her own struggles."

    old "Were they two fools, each stumbling into something?"
    new "Were they two fools, each stumbling into something?"

    old "Sarah sighed and composed herself."
    new "Sarah sighed and composed herself."

    old "It didn't matter. Not now, not anymore."
    new "It didn't matter. Not now, not anymore."

    old "The ceremony was under way, and they would be married. To call things off now would be unforgivable."
    new "The ceremony was under way, and they would be married. To call things off now would be unforgivable."

    old "Sarah could hear the high priest begin to utter the words."
    new "Sarah could hear the high priest begin to utter the words."

    old "She had been here before, she realized."
    new "She had been here before, she realized."

    old "But then, she had been in the audience."
    new "But then, she had been in the audience."

    old "Some nobles, of high enough birth, earned the right to marry at the royal court. Before the king."
    new "Some nobles, of high enough birth, earned the right to marry at the royal court. Before the king."

    old "Sarah could remember her younger self, sitting and spectating."
    new "Sarah could remember her younger self, sitting and spectating."

    old "When her mother had still been alive, she had once been so overcome with excitement, that her mother had almost send her back to her room."
    new "When her mother had still been alive, she had once been so overcome with excitement, that her mother had almost send her back to her room."

    old "The sight of the dresses, the ceremony, the handsome husbands..."
    new "The sight of the dresses, the ceremony, the handsome husbands..."

    old "For a lifetime, she had wished for nothing more."
    new "For a lifetime, she had wished for nothing more."

    old "Now, she suffered having it."
    new "Now, she suffered having it."

    old "The priest clasped his hands together."
    new "The priest clasped his hands together."

    old "First he turned to Marion."
    new "First he turned to Marion."

    old "High Priest\" \"Do you you take Sarah Rose as your wife before all the Gods?"
    new "High Priest\" \"Do you you take Sarah Rose as your wife before all the Gods?"

    old "Then the High Priest turned to her."
    new "Then the High Priest turned to her."

    old "High Priest\" \"Do you take Marion Achillea as your husband before all the Gods?"
    new "High Priest\" \"Do you take Marion Achillea as your husband before all the Gods?"

    old "For the faintest moment, Sarah considered her answer."
    new "For the faintest moment, Sarah considered her answer."

    old "Then she gave the only answer she knew she could."
    new "Then she gave the only answer she knew she could."

    old "The priest clapsed his hands together again."
    new "The priest clapsed his hands together again."

    old "High Priest\" \"Then before all Gods and all gathered witnesses, I declare you married."
    new "High Priest\" \"Then before all Gods and all gathered witnesses, I declare you married."

    old "Sarah could hear the crowd explode into an almost violent cheer."
    new "Sarah could hear the crowd explode into an almost violent cheer."

    old "She herself only looked straight at her now husband."
    new "She herself only looked straight at her now husband."

    old "Marion only smiled in that same, perfect, cultivated way."
    new "Marion only smiled in that same, perfect, cultivated way."

    old "As the servants rushed the hall, they began their impressive labor of transforming the wedding room into a feast hall."
    new "As the servants rushed the hall, they began their impressive labor of transforming the wedding room into a feast hall."

    old "Chairs made way for long tables and benches."
    new "Chairs made way for long tables and benches."

    old "It was a marvel to behold, if only for the skill with which they did it."
    new "It was a marvel to behold, if only for the skill with which they did it."

    old "Sarah and Marion, as expected, were given the seats of honor."
    new "Sarah and Marion, as expected, were given the seats of honor."

    old "Sarah saw Thomas, sitting a small distance away from her."
    new "Sarah saw Thomas, sitting a small distance away from her."

    old "He smiled, but she imagined seeing a pain in his eyes."
    new "He smiled, but she imagined seeing a pain in his eyes."

    old "Looking back at Marion, she saw him looking about the room."
    new "Looking back at Marion, she saw him looking about the room."

    old "Quite the turn out."
    new "Quite the turn out."

    old "I would have hoped so."
    new "I would have hoped so."

    old "All the Old Houses showed, that's good."
    new "All the Old Houses showed, that's good."

    old "I thought everyone would be here."
    new "I thought everyone would be here."

    old "A few did not attend."
    new "A few did not attend."

    old "Anything we need to worry about?"
    new "Anything we need to worry about?"

    old "Marion laughed."
    new "Marion laughed."

    old "No, some small houses, eager to make a statement I think."
    new "No, some small houses, eager to make a statement I think."

    old "We have the Old Houses, most of the Great Lords and even most of the Provincial Lords."
    new "We have the Old Houses, most of the Great Lords and even most of the Provincial Lords."

    old "Sarah scanned the room and quickly saw he was right."
    new "Sarah scanned the room and quickly saw he was right."

    old "You're..."
    new "You're..."

    old "Quite perceptive."
    new "Quite perceptive."

    old "Well, when you get raised to look at those noble faces all day, you develop a talent I suppose."
    new "Well, when you get raised to look at those noble faces all day, you develop a talent I suppose."

    old "You're not that different, I imagine?"
    new "You're not that different, I imagine?"

    old "Sarah nodded, realizing she quickly saw the same that he did."
    new "Sarah nodded, realizing she quickly saw the same that he did."

    old "We're missing...Greytower...Riverbend...and..."
    new "We're missing...Greytower...Riverbend...and..."

