    new "It's clever."

    old "Ah, you approve of my decision?"
    new "Ah, you approve of my decision?"

    old "I thought you would be mad with me."
    new "I thought you would be mad with me."

    old "Sarah smiled at him. She could play the game too."
    new "Sarah smiled at him. She could play the game too."

    old "Mad? For what reason?"
    new "Mad? For what reason?"

    old "Well, you and Varga were quite close, no?"
    new "Well, you and Varga were quite close, no?"

    old "There it was. Jealousy. The hint of something untoward."
    new "There it was. Jealousy. The hint of something untoward."

    old "We were friends."
    new "We were friends."

    old "I'm sure you have friends."
    new "I'm sure you have friends."

    old "But let me be clear with you as well."
    new "But let me be clear with you as well."

    old "Our marriage will mark a new time in each of our lives."
    new "Our marriage will mark a new time in each of our lives."

    old "We cannot keep playing at childishness."
    new "We cannot keep playing at childishness."

    old "I mean that we must be proper in our conduct, as well as our appearance."
    new "I mean that we must be proper in our conduct, as well as our appearance."

    old "Friends...well, I think it would be better for you to keep the kinds of friends that are proper for a wife."
    new "Friends...well, I think it would be better for you to keep the kinds of friends that are proper for a wife."

    old "Proper?"
    new "Proper?"

    old "Yes. No need to give these vultures any reason to gossip. They do enough of that on their own."
    new "Yes. No need to give these vultures any reason to gossip. They do enough of that on their own."

    old "How easily he asserted his control over her."
    new "How easily he asserted his control over her."

    old "A part of her wanted to resist it, but Sarah also knew that he was right."
    new "A part of her wanted to resist it, but Sarah also knew that he was right."

    old "The rules that governed them, were changing."
    new "The rules that governed them, were changing."

    old "She was his wife, and a Rosannian wife was expected to show defference to her husband."
    new "She was his wife, and a Rosannian wife was expected to show defference to her husband."

