    new "Friends, kin, I welcome all your kind words, but I fear to admit I have had my fill."

    old "My fill of food and my fill of kindness."
    new "My fill of food and my fill of kindness."

    old "Please, I beg of you all, forgive a newly married man for wanting to eagerly depart and get to other business with his new wife."
    new "Please, I beg of you all, forgive a newly married man for wanting to eagerly depart and get to other business with his new wife."

    old "In the crowd, more men than women laughed."
    new "In the crowd, more men than women laughed."

    old "Ushered away by the servants, they arrived back at Sarah's room."
    new "Ushered away by the servants, they arrived back at Sarah's room."

    old "Every step there, she could feel her heart tremble, her hands shake."
    new "Every step there, she could feel her heart tremble, her hands shake."

    old "Near the end, she imagined her feet like lead."
    new "Near the end, she imagined her feet like lead."

    old "Sarah knew this too was part of it."
    new "Sarah knew this too was part of it."

